issueOrPullRequest.body:
This pull request fixes dependency warnings by raising the optional litellm constraint to >=1.80.10,<2 and regenerating uv.lock:

```
================================================================== warnings summary ===================================================================
.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/litellm/types/llms/anthropic.py:531
  ~/openai-agents-python/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/litellm/types/llms/anthropic.py:531: PydanticDeprecatedSince20: Support f
or class-based `config` is deprecated, use ConfigDict instead. Deprecated in Pydantic V2.0 to be removed in V3.0. See Pydantic V2 Migration Guide at ht
tps://errors.pydantic.dev/2.12/migration/
    class AnthropicResponseContentBlockToolUse(BaseModel):

.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/litellm/types/rag.py:181
  ~/openai-agents-python/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/litellm/types/rag.py:181: PydanticDeprecatedSince20: Support for class-ba
sed `config` is deprecated, use ConfigDict instead. Deprecated in Pydantic V2.0 to be removed in V3.0. See Pydantic V2 Migration Guide at https://error
s.pydantic.dev/2.12/migration/
    class RAGIngestRequest(BaseModel):

-- Docs: https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html
==================================================== 1458 passed, 4 skipped, 2 warnings in 34.88s =====================================================
```

The lock update pulls in litellm 1.80.13 (which replaces deprecated Pydantic Config usage) and adjusts Python 3.14 resolution markers along with grpcio splits for >=3.14 vs older interpreters. These changes quiet the PydanticDeprecatedSince20 warnings seen during tests while keeping compatibility across supported Python versions.
issueOrPullRequest.title: fix: bump litellm to resolve pydantic deprecation warnings
